OrganizationFormalName: National Park Service Water Resources Division
MonitoringLocationName: Courthouse Wash Above Colorado River Near Moab, UT
MonitoringLocationDescriptionText: This station is at Courthouse Wash above Colorado River near Moab, Utah. This site is approximately 1.3 kilometers upstream of the confluence with Colorado River. Latitude and longitude coordinates were compiled from previous studies or topographic map interpolation. This station has additional IDs and names: USGS NWIS Site No. 09183000, Courthouse Wash Near Moab, UT; USGS-NWIS Site No.  383646109344701, Courthouse Wash above Colorado River near Moab, UT; and Utah Dept. of Environmental Quality No. 5995240, Courthouse Wash .5mi ab Colorado R at USGS.

OrganizationFormalName: National Park Service Water Resources Division
MonitoringLocationName: Sleepy Hollow Spring in Upper Courthouse Wash
MonitoringLocationDescriptionText: This station is at Sleepy Hollow Spring in Upper Courthouse Wash.
